result.execSummary:
The defendant Rachel K Elston was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess/Illegally Obtained Prescription, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 450.11(7)(h).
  • Possession of Cocaine/Coca, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(c).
  • Possess/Illegally Obtained Prescription, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 450.11(7)(h).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

[Reserve Judge Sarah O'Brien presiding for BrIV]
Defendant Rachel K Elston in court with Attorney Jennifer L. Weber. ADA Jeffrey Martin Shock appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Weber: Have reached a resolution, however was unable to complete paperwork today. Requests matter be set for plea/sentencing in a couple weeks - will be stipulated plea/sentencing
Upon questioning of the Court, Atty Weber indicates that she could possibly proceed today, but do not have jury instructions or elements on amended charges as they are not available on standard forms
off-record: 2:37 - 2:38 pm for Court/Counsel to research jury instructions
Clerk provides Atty Weber with jur instruction, she requests time to complete paperwork
Recess: 2:38 pm Reconvene: 2:46 pm - Appearances the same. 
ADA Shock submits AMENDED criminal complaint; Service of AMENDED complaint admitted; reading waived

Constitutional rights given; plea of "No Contest" entered on Counts #1, #2 & #3; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; Court finds the plea has been entered freely, voluntarily, intelligently and accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders JOC entered.

On Counts #1, #2 & #3, the Court withholds sentence, places Defendant on Probation for 2 years, each count, concurrent, with conditions:
--AODA Assessment & Follow Through with any recommended treatment, per Agent
--To undergo any other assessment, treatment or counseling as required per Agent
--To obtain/maintain employment and/or education program, per Agent
--Maintain absolute sobriety
--No possession or consumption of alcohol
--Monthly testing for illegal drug use
--To pay costs of $729 ($243 each count)
--To pay $600 DNA Surcharge ($200 each count)

Days credit for time already served: 1 days

case called at 1:32pm. 
Defendant Rachel K Elston appears via videoconferencing from the Jefferson County Jail, in custody, with Attorney Elizabeth Svehlek (PD will appoint counsel).  Public Service Prosecutor Melanie Flint appears for the State of Wisconsin.  

On agreement of counsel, the Court finds that the videoconferencing system is sight and sound sufficient. 

Service of Complaint admitted, reading waived, the charge and maximum penalties are recited. 
Preliminary Hearing time limits are waived by both parties.

The Court requires a $5,000 signature bond, with conditions:
--no contact with Jaye Kamuchey
--no possession of alcohol with the exception of Ms. Elston being required to do so based on employment
--no consumption of alcohol
--no presence in bars, taverns, or liquor stores except if employed in such a capacity as requiring such a presence in such a place for work purposes
--no ingestion of controlled substances without a valid prescription
--not to possess any prescription medication while this case pends, whether or not there is a prescription that has been issued for it
recess 1:42pm.
